<br>
I know the League was formed in the great cave in the EC tunnel in October (I think). Jaynus was the Guildmaster, and... Valdria? (or someone whose name started with a &quot;V&quot;)... was his co-leader.... Gray was an officer, I think. I don't remember any of the others, sadly (I was an Iksar Shaman at the time, and unaware of events outside of Kunark).<br>
<br>
Jaynus and his co-leader (I think they were a RL couple) quickly found themselves at odds with the rest of the guild--I believe it had to do with their vision of the guild in terms of role-playing. Not wishing to compromise that vision, they left the server altogether, and passed leadership on to Gray. Many, many months later, Jaynus' co-leader returned, and was welcomed warmly by Gray back into the guild. I think she ended up stepping on a number of toes, though, because she ended up leaving rather quickly.<br>
<br>
LoS' first raid was into Mistmoore--it was disasterous as I recall <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   . And I have to say, FnF quickly outdistanced LoS in terms of levels and raiding. The majority of the League was happy to focus more on RP and exploration, than levelling. There were a number of exceptions though (Biji comes to mind), and very shortly, tensions began to grow between the more RP oriented members, and the more Gamer-oriented ones (an old story on FV), which led to an exodus of many of the highest-level members of the guild.<br>
<br>
Zsuzsana (whom I've seen back in the world recently) could tell you more about the details of our alliance with Blackened Roses--it was the only guild alliance we had in those days. It started mainly due to the friendship between Gray and Zsu--eventually, Zsu decided that merging BR with LoS would serve everyone better, and joined LoS as an officer. Many of the BR members, though, were bitter about the whole turn of events, and decided to keep BR alive without Zsu. BR quickly degenerated, and fell apart.<br>
<br>
I somewhat recall a guildwar of sorts with the Council of Silver Griffons, but I really don't remember the details.<br>
<br>
As for dates, I'm sorry, I don't have any <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   . Sadly, I did not keep the timeline I had created for the guild after I left--no one in the guild really seemed to care much about it besides me.... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=makrazhat>Makrazhat</A> at: 9/14/03 2:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dididaryth>Didi D Aryth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Worshipping Tallonar since 3160</span><br>  Posts: 1375<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/03 4:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4898.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Seeking a history of the League of Shadows</span><hr size=1> The LoS was founded on the first day guilds could be founded on FV - anybody know when this was?<br>
